  "issue_title": "feat(watchlist): show why each PR is in the Pull Requests tab",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nAfter #784, the Watchlist *Pull Requests* tab auto-shows PRs from any starred PR, watched miner, or watched repository \u2014 but the resulting list is flat. There is no visual indication of *why* each PR is shown.\n\nAdd a small **Source** indicator (a column in the list view, an inline chip group on the card view) that displays up to three badges per row, one for each source the PR matches:\n\n- **Starred** \u2014 the user explicitly starred this PR.\n- **Miner** \u2014 the PR's author is in the user's watched-miners list.\n- **Repo** \u2014 the PR's repository is in the user's watched-repositories list.\n\nA PR can match multiple sources and should show all matching badges side-by-side.\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe most common confusion after #784 is *\"why is this PR here? I don't remember starring it.\"* Users have to mentally cross-reference their three watchlists to figure it out, which undermines the value of auto-show.\n\nA Source indicator directly visualizes the original ask of #784 (*\"auto displaying all PRs for any miner or repo added to the watch list\"*) by making the relationship explicit on every row. It also gives onboarding users and reviewers a single-screenshot understanding of how the tab works.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis enhancement was discussed with and approved by the maintainer in chat ahead of filing.\n",
